        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=61723&amp;TOPIC_ID=7414&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Fear+Kiting+inside&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Echo caverns on the underbulk side.  In the room before the Task Master's room there are seven spawns of various types (underbulks,stonegrabbers, fungal fiends).  The first spawn is located at the top of the tunnel at the entrance to the room.  Pull this one with darkness, sic pet, invoke fear and he will path back down the tunnel and then hang a left (if he gets that far).  The mob will enter the room with the four underbulks (you passed through this room to get to this point) but will not aggro them.  </P><P>Pull the other six spawns using the same method.  The next two are located close together and you will get a double pull (at least to level 48) so you will have to use the ST pull method.  Using the 44 pet I didn't even bother to follow them down the tunnel once I feared.  I just sat back down and continued to med until I got the xp message and pulled the next one.  If fear wore off fairly early into the fight I would refear but generally one cast was enough and the pet (with augment on) will eat them up. </P><P>The loot here is great.  Stonegrabbers drop cash, up to 10pp, and the other types drop body parts some of which sell for several platinum each. Experience is also very nice.  A full round of seven spawns will net you about 2 to 2.5 blues.  Only drawbacks are the slow respawn time, around 12 minutes, and the popularity of the area.  If you play in the early morning you can usually find this spot uncamped.</P><P>Even with the slow respawn time I was able to complete 44-47 in about 20 hours total playing time(this inclued doing the four underbulks every now and then to supplement xp).  The room goes mostly light blue at 48 and though it still generates about 1 blue of xp per round it is just too slow and I left. </P><P>One last thing to look out for are Trillcor and Fireclaw, named fungal fiend and underbulk respectively.  They are pretty tough especially since they can not be snared, rooted, or feared.  I was able to take them but it is very mana costly.  Fireclaw drops a couple of decent low level twink items but Trillcor drops nothing.  They can pop at any of the seven spawns points on a random basis.  Depending on which one of the spots they pop in you may be able to just ignor them if you so desire.  </P><P>In my experience, however, they seemed to always pop in a spot I had to pull past so I had to take them out.  If you decide to try them be advised that in addition to the above mentioned invulnerabilities Fireclaw has very high fire resistance and Trillcor has very high poison resistance.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

